detailed analysis of the problem: The test errors indicate that the Flask application cannot find the template file 'dashboard.html' when rendering the dashboard page. This causes a jinja2.exceptions.TemplateNotFound error. The source code calls render_template('dashboard.html', ...) in the dashboard() function, but the template file 'dashboard.html' is missing from the expected templates directory. This missing template file leads to all tests failing when trying to access the root URL '/' and render the dashboard page. To fix this, the 'dashboard.html' template and other required HTML templates must be created and placed in the Flask application's templates folder so that render_template can locate and render them properly.
